Date: Fri, 19 Apr 2013 18:17:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 046/257] dma: keystone: fix descriptor type for host

The chan_start() function uses wrong value (1 - reserved) for HOST descriptor type
instead of 0. This fixes the issue.

Signed-off-by: Murali Karicheri <m-karicheri2@ti.com>
(cherry picked from commit 05fa74188ac609cdc70331db01b5e47f8e2dddd8)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/dma/keystone-pktdma.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/keystone-pktdma.c b/drivers/dma/keystone-pktdma.c
index 351c6d3..804f77b 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/keystone-pktdma.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/keystone-pktdma.c
@@ -54,7 +54,7 @@
 #define DESC_FLOWTAG_MASK	BITS(8)
 #define DESC_FLOWTAG_SHIFT	16
 #define DESC_LEN_MASK		BITS(22)
-#define DESC_TYPE_HOST		1
+#define DESC_TYPE_HOST		0
 #define DESC_TYPE_SHIFT		26
 
 #define DMA_DEFAULT_NUM_DESCS	128
